data.title: Dublinforum.net
data.meta_description:
There are some places where it says....''do not feed the seagulls''......

where there is nothing written down.....I feed the seagulls, as is my right to do so......

am I ''right''......?
data.text:
Originally posted by Twobob View Post

Standing in the passage last Friday with some woman looking for my vote...few crows flying past and a crap right on her head ...the curses out of her ....she asks me for a bit of tissue....so I had to tell her ...their to far away and she would'nt actually know which one done it ...: .

Originally posted by DAMNTHEWEATHER View Post

nothing wrong with a 'few birds' no...a few bird is ok in any mans book....but....I cudda swore we were talkin about you feedin seagulls a minneh ago....that's not a 'few birds' now is it ? no.....that's nuisance birds who will learn your feeding habits very fast and tell all their mates....bit like ants behave when they discover the way into yer preserves cupboard and then go spread the word.....not easy to get rid of. So be sensible Quinner and leave the sea gulls by the sea.

Originally posted by DAMNTHEWEATHER View Post

Now yiv gone inta pinch of salt routine again. Anyway, a few mins or not.....try think of the poor busted who has to live with your badly trained gulls for the rest of the year....ye never thought of that did you ? Oh no....as long as you're alright Jack.....the rest can do what ye told the lift manager fella in yer last post.....Yeah... I'm alright Jack...flock you !!!

Originally posted by quinner View Post

a couple of years before I retired.....a new manager came on the company I worked for....

a few days later he rang my mobile and told me to go to a particular job......my reply was...''fuck off''......as I disconnected the phone.....

he then went to the area manager.....

he said I am not having engineers speak to me like that......

thearea manager said, who was that and what did you say....

he said, I told Quinner to go and do a job at x location......

the area manager then said......you should have asked him, he is a very obliging peson....

telling him is a waste of time.......he would even tell me to ''fuck off''.....

the moral of the story......

anybody, that speaks to me like that will always get the same reply.......

no matter who they are.....

Originally posted by quinner View Post

yes Twobob......

I worked in the construction industry for most of my life......

when you speak to somebody that you don't know......or want something done.

you introduce yourself.........

you ask politely......

you say thank you.......

by the way......that manager didn't last long.......I never actually met him, he worked in the Cardiff office..........I very seldom went over there....

it was a nice company to work for......five times I worked for them.....

Originally posted by Twobob View Post

I worked for a crowd up till 18 mths back ....this one [ lets just say one of our european cousins ] clicked her fingers at me with her arm raised , I just stood and stared her out of it ...she never crossed my path again....i'm f@?@?d if any one is going to raise them selves off my back .

Originally posted by quinner View Post

lol.....Twobob, I have had a great working life......the job on the whole was fun......if I was fit enough I would have stayed on after I reached retiring age........

alas, I had to go........I don't really miss it though.....

I meet up with some of the lads now and again if they are in my area......we go and have a breakfast and a chat......

I worked mainly for SCHINDLER LIFTS a Swiss company.......and then for THYSSEN KRUPP ELEVATORS a German company....
